<p>This second selection is from the â€œSaga of Eledd.â€ Eledd is a princess whose brother Cynddylan has died in battle, which leaves her and Powys without their truest protector. It is unclear in which battle Cynddylan fell, but the cycle of poems about Eledd suggest that he died in an otherwise unknown battle at the river Tern in Shropshire (Welsh Sir Amwythig) â€“ the other source for Cynddylan, a marwnad or death poem, suggest that he was an ally of King Penda of Mercia against King Oswald of Northumbria. In this selection, Eledd mourns her brother through a mourning of his once-bright hall now desolate and run-down.</p>

